<subSubSection id="3387654DFFDEFFF3FF78F962FC421FBE" box="[151,900,1699,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="7B2236C6FFDEFFF3FF78F962FC421FBE" blockId="5.[151,1436,1699,1977]" box="[151,900,1699,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">
<typeStatus id="A4268864FFDEFFF3FF78F962FF091FBE" box="[151,207,1699,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="BC9D4D45FFDEFFF3FEDAF962FDD71FBE" authority="Golovatch &amp; Vandenspiegel, 2022" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Vandenspiegel" authorityYear="2022" box="[309,529,1699,1725]" class="Diplopoda" family="Pachybolidae" genus="Costabolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirobolida" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baculus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FEDAF962FDD71FBE" box="[309,529,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Costabolus baculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FDF6F962FDB41FBE" bold="true" box="[537,626,1699,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="52DA57AFFFDEFFF3FDF6F962FDB41FBE" box="[537,626,1699,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by present designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3387654DFFDEFFF3FF28F906FD631E06" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7B2236C6FFDEFFF3FF28F906FD631E06" blockId="5.[151,1436,1699,1977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FF28F906FECB1FE2" bold="true" box="[199,269,1735,1761]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Name</emphasis>
. Reflecting the longitudinal costae/ribs on the metazonae, and ʻ-bolusʼ, a common suffix for genus-group names in the 
<taxonomicName id="BC9D4D45FFDEFFF3FEC3F92AFE741E06" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1895" box="[300,434,1771,1797]" class="Diplopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirobolida" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Spirobolida</taxonomicName>
; masculine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3387654DFFDEFFF3FF28F8CFFB3E1E96" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7B2236C6FFDEFFF3FF28F8CFFB3E1E96" blockId="5.[151,1436,1699,1977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FF28F8CFFEFC1E2B" bold="true" box="[199,314,1806,1832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Distinguished from all pachybolid genera but 
<taxonomicName id="BC9D4D45FFDEFFF3FCABF8CEFC161E2A" authority="Golovatch &amp; Vandenspiegel, 2022" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Vandenspiegel" authorityYear="2022" box="[836,976,1807,1833]" genus="Carinobolus" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FCABF8CEFC161E2A" box="[836,976,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Carinobolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FC39F8CEFBF81E2A" bold="true" box="[982,1086,1807,1833]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="52DA57AFFFDEFFF3FC39F8CEFBF81E2A" box="[982,1086,1807,1833]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by strongly crested metazonae, from 
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FF3BF8F2FE931E4E" box="[212,341,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Carinobolu</emphasis>
s 
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FE89F8F2FE091E4E" bold="true" box="[358,463,1843,1869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">gen. nov.</emphasis>
by the crests being simple, even, not bimodal, by the presence of prominent prefemoral protuberances on male legs 2 and of prominent coxal protuberances on male legs 3, and the anterior gonopods being subtriangular in overall shape, 
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FE1EF8BAFDCE1E97" box="[497,520,1915,1940]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">vs</emphasis>
. rather palm-shaped in 
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FCFDF8BAFC551E96" box="[786,915,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Carinobolu</emphasis>
s 
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FC4AF8BAFBC81E96" bold="true" box="[933,1038,1915,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">gen. nov.</emphasis>
See also Key below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3387654DFFDEFFF3FF28F85FFB9E1EBA" box="[199,1112,1950,1977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7B2236C6FFDEFFF3FF28F85FFB9E1EBA" blockId="5.[151,1436,1699,1977]" box="[199,1112,1950,1977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDEFFF3FF28F85FFEA71EBB" bold="true" box="[199,353,1950,1976]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus id="A4268864FFDEFFF3FD8FF85EFD561EBA" box="[608,656,1951,1977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">type</typeStatus>
locality in southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="038A7656FFDEFFF3FC4DF85EFC301EBA" box="[930,1014,1951,1977]" name="Nigeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="E3A62A43FFDEFFF3FBE9F85EFB8C1EBA" box="[1030,1098,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1191,1215]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1168]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1436,181,1168]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Distributions of Carinobolus complex sp. nov. and Costabolus baculus sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610066/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="102">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
